<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-02-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-02-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1178" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1178">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/33270:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Harold H.
                                    Tittmann</persName>, Assistant to the Personal Representative of
                                President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName> to <persName>Pope
                                    Pius XII</persName>, to the Secretary of State</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Vatican City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-18">February 18,
                                1944</date>.<lb/>[Received February 18—9:02 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>51. My 44, 11th.<note n="10" xml:id="d1178fn1">Not printed.</note>
                            Vatican note today states according to reliable information just now
                            reaching Holy See there are no German artillery positions or other
                            military equipment in proximity of Papal Villa Castel Gandolfo which can
                            constitute objective for Allied Air Forces and asks that my Government
                            be informed in order that bombing of that zone be avoided and danger to
                            Villa, which at present is sheltering several thousand civilians
                            evacuated from neighboring towns, be removed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Tittmann</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>